{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-event-js","path":"/event/artist-talk-by-mario-santamaria/","result":{"data":{"contentfulEvent":{"title":"Artist Talk by Mario Santamaria","date":"2022-04-28T19:00","endTime":null,"openEnd":true,"entryfee":null,"eventSeries":{"slug":"rosa","name":"/rosa"},"tags":null,"subtitleShortDescription":{"childMarkdownRemark":{"html":"<p>Event at /rosa, Rosa-Luxemburg-Strasse 35, Berlin-Mitte</p>"}},"description":{"childMarkdownRemark":{"html":"<p><strong>Artist Talk by Mario Santamaría</strong> <br>\nThursday, 28 April 2022 7pm</p>\n<p>We are very happy to have artist Mario Santamaría give a talk at /rosa on 28 April at 7 pm. Mario Santamaria's practice engages with narratives told about technologies and the manifestations of networks that are often claimed to be disembodied and ephemeral.</p>\n<p>His 2019 work Cloudplexity - a series of drawings made to represent\nthe Internet extracted from the U.S. Patent database - has just recently been on display at C/O in Berlin. At /rosa Santamaria will talk about his practice and introduce us to some of his new and lesser known works.</p>\n<p><strong>Come join us for the talk and drinks on Thursday, 28 April, 7 pm at /rosa, Rosa-Luxemburg-Straße 35, 10178 Berlin.</strong></p>\n<p>— please wear an FFP2 mask —</p>"}},"furtherInformationBlocks":[{"id":"9d959d93-ca3c-5502-87bc-5c64032b10aa","title":"About the artist","childContentfulContentBlockBlockContentTextNode":{"id":"a27b6dd5-07ac-5e1b-af43-b17ff82c0efe","childMarkdownRemark":{"html":"<p><a href=\"http://www.mariosantamaria.net/\">Mario Santamaría</a> (Burgos, 1985) is a visual artist who works with a wide range of media, frequently using photography, video, performance, websites and online interventions. Co-founder of the space Trama34 (2016) in L’Hospitalet de Llobregat and lecturer at Elisava University in Barcelona, for several years he was a collaborator of The Influencers festival and\ncurator of the Internet Yami-Ichi (Internet Black Market) at CCCB and Matadero Madrid. He has been artist in residence at Hangar Barcelona, HISK Gantes or Sarai New Delhi and finalist of the prestigious Post-Photography Prototyping award of Fotomuseum Winterthur. His work is part of the anthology Watched! by the Hasselblad Foundation. His work has been exhibited in institutions such as: MACBA Barcelona, ZKM Karlsruhe, WKV Stuttgart, C/O Berlin, La Casa Encendida Madrid, CENART Mexico, Or Gallery Berlin, Arebyte London and Aksioma Ljubljana, among others.</p>"}}}],"featuredImage":{"gatsbyImageData":{"images":{"sources":[{"srcSet":"https://images.ctfassets.net/31ro1qkhyo69/4ishkEfLLR5sm8vmJXn596/3189c2d5858ed063cd2c9a5af33cb5f7/rafa-castels-escritorio_web_copy.jpg?w=750&h=494&q=100&fm=webp&bg=transparent 750w,\nhttps://images.ctfassets.net/31ro1qkhyo69/4ishkEfLLR5sm8vmJXn596/3189c2d5858ed063cd2c9a5af33cb5f7/rafa-castels-escritorio_web_copy.jpg?w=1050&h=692&q=100&fm=webp&bg=transparent 1050w,\nhttps://images.ctfassets.net/31ro1qkhyo69/4ishkEfLLR5sm8vmJXn596/3189c2d5858ed063cd2c9a5af33cb5f7/rafa-castels-escritorio_web_copy.jpg?w=1080&h=712&q=100&fm=webp&bg=transparent 1080w,\nhttps://images.ctfassets.net/31ro1qkhyo69/4ishkEfLLR5sm8vmJXn596/3189c2d5858ed063cd2c9a5af33cb5f7/rafa-castels-escritorio_web_copy.jpg?w=1134&h=747&q=100&fm=webp&bg=transparent 1134w","sizes":"(min-width: 1050px) 1050px, 100vw","type":"image/webp"}],"fallback":{"src":"https://images.ctfassets.net/31ro1qkhyo69/4ishkEfLLR5sm8vmJXn596/3189c2d5858ed063cd2c9a5af33cb5f7/rafa-castels-escritorio_web_copy.jpg?w=1050&h=692&fl=progressive&q=100&fm=jpg&bg=transparent","srcSet":"https://images.ctfassets.net/31ro1qkhyo69/4ishkEfLLR5sm8vmJXn596/3189c2d5858ed063cd2c9a5af33cb5f7/rafa-castels-escritorio_web_copy.jpg?w=750&h=494&fl=progressive&q=100&fm=jpg&bg=transparent 750w,\nhttps://images.ctfassets.net/31ro1qkhyo69/4ishkEfLLR5sm8vmJXn596/3189c2d5858ed063cd2c9a5af33cb5f7/rafa-castels-escritorio_web_copy.jpg?w=1050&h=692&fl=progressive&q=100&fm=jpg&bg=tran